<dec f='include/freetype2/freetype/freetype.h' l='3640' type='FT_Error FT_Select_Charmap(FT_Face face, FT_Encoding encoding)'/>
<doc f='include/freetype2/freetype/freetype.h' l='3609'>/**************************************************************************
   *
   * @function:
   *   FT_Select_Charmap
   *
   * @description:
   *   Select a given charmap by its encoding tag (as listed in
   *   `freetype.h`).
   *
   * @inout:
   *   face ::
   *     A handle to the source face object.
   *
   * @input:
   *   encoding ::
   *     A handle to the selected encoding.
   *
   * @return:
   *   FreeType error code.  0~means success.
   *
   * @note:
   *   This function returns an error if no charmap in the face corresponds
   *   to the encoding queried here.
   *
   *   Because many fonts contain more than a single cmap for Unicode
   *   encoding, this function has some special code to select the one that
   *   covers Unicode best (&apos;best&apos; in the sense that a UCS-4 cmap is
   *   preferred to a UCS-2 cmap).  It is thus preferable to @FT_Set_Charmap
   *   in this case.
   */</doc>
